1+ This is what the Lord God showed me: behold, a basket of summer fruit. 
2And he said, + “Amos, what do you see?” And I said, + “A basket of summer fruit.” Then the Lord said to me,
3+ The songs of the temple+ + shall become wailings+  in that day,”
4Hear this, + you who trample on the needy
5saying, “When will + the new moon be over,
6that we may buy the poor for + silver
7The Lord has sworn by + the pride of Jacob:
8+ Shall not the land tremble on this account,
9“And on that day,” declares the Lord God,
10+ I will turn your feasts into mourning
11“Behold, the days are coming,” declares the Lord God,
12+ They shall wander from sea to sea,
13+ “In that day the lovely virgins and the young men
14Those who swear by + the Guilt of Samaria,
